TUBERCULOSIS TRANSMISSION RISK IN AIDS PATIENTS (4)
===================================================
A previous posting notes:
>You may wish to revise your guidelines in light of the fact that
>the CXR [chest X-ray] of an HIV + individual with TB disease may
>often not only not appear unusual but may even appear entirely
>normal ....

Perhaps this is a result of deficient cellular immunity which translates
as an absence of granuloma?
--
Raymond G. Whitham, MD, DVM
